EXECUTION
In case the run dies in the middle, you can restore this file by closing any open tags. Typically, the only tags you will have to close are CYCLE and TruchasData: </CYCLE> </TruchasData>
or TIMESTEP and TruchasData: </TIMESTEP> </TruchasData>
Most other tags write their information in a single pass and should already be closed.
It is also possible that some of your variable data in the lookaside files '*.ts.#####.xml' are incomplete, but there is no way to recover this data since it was never written. The OutputParser.py should ignore these files, but if it doesn't, You can just delete the last timestep tag from this file.
